You can buy clothes, armor, cars, ships, and a slew of other things. But the one thing I love the most is the dungeons. You go to a mission &quot;terminal&quot; and recieve a mission. (Kind of like EQ's mission givers.) On your compass, (no sense heading by the way - compass works all the time) you will be directed to the dungeon. <br>
Dungeons can be small or they can be huge. Each one is different and is randomized every time. There are team dungeons and single dungeons. Though, you can invite a friend to your single dungeon at any time provided they have the key.<br>
Graphically, I found this game to be a lot better than EQ. There were more clothes appearances and weapon appearances. The animations are terrific. You arent stuck to one animation for melee battle. You will pierce and slash your enemy in different ways. There are a slew of emotes you can use in this game ranging from reading, to drinking, to doing the YMCA dance.<br>
You can own your own apartment as well! Each apartment holds 30 items, and you can furnish it in any way you like. There are two different types of apartments basic and luxury. Basic apartments have 2 floors and can hold 30 items. Luxury apartments are huge with a pool, 30 item storage limit, and more. Though, luxury apartments were only available by pre ordering the newest expansion pack, Shadowlands.<br>
There are 200 levels, and 10 shadow levels. Shadow levels are the same as levels, only you must learn more about the shadowlands or fight in the shadowlands. There is a HUGE collection of skills to train in as well. <br>
There is around 13 professions to choose from. Each profession is unique and provide many ways to play the game.<br>
I chose a Keeper to play as, in EQ terms that would be a paladin/bard. They heal themselves for a small amount every 6 or so seconds, and are great with two handed weapons such as heavy axes.<br>
The only things I found to be horrible was the player UI. It is not very customizable, and you cannot import your own UI like you can in EQ. I also found the game to be pretty easy. Though, I have only tried the keeper out so far, so I cannot say how it is for other professions.<br>
The last thing I did not like was the roleplay - there was none! Though, there was no roleplay, the game is not filled with losers trying to scam you. The people I have met have all been friendly and willing to help me out, and I have done my best to return the favor.<br>
All in all, if you are into a sci-fi setting, are bored of EQ, or just want to try out something new, then Anarchy Online is for you. It is also cheaper than EQ! =D<br>
